1.1 Decision API
Decision is the level at which rules and thresholds are applied.
It is the lever using which scoring aggregation and workflow
triggers are also assigned. Decisions can be real time/batch. Real
Time decisions are used for configuring realtime rules on
transactions. Decision also supports running and evaluating
transactions in batch mode over a specified duration e.g. daily /
weekly / monthly. This results in using a transaction profile at
an account/vpa level for EOD/EOW/EOM. The same can be configured
by adding additional attributes while configuring the
decision.Further, we can also set storing logic, processing logic
and dependants logic to fully configure a decision in Drona Pay.
The API supports CRUD operations and the details on the same is
given below:
> `[POST /decision]` to add a decision
> `[PUT /decision/decisionid]` to edit a decision
> `[DELETE /decision/decisionid]` to delete a decision
> `[GET /decision/decisionid]` to fetch a decision
