The Score Request, Score Response & Score Events API Flow are
depicted below and form the bulk of the communication with the
Drona Pay Risk Scoring system.
Score Events can also be delivered via a webhook, if the
deployment requires it.
b. Authentication
When you are ready to start the risk scoring process, send us an
email and we will send you test credentials. Your email should
include the IP address from which the score requests will be
initiated (this IP Address will be whitelisted on our server). We
will provide the API key and the URL. When you initiate any API
call, you will need to pass the key in the header, as shown below:
curl -X request POST \
https://testscore.dronapay.com/score \
--header ''Content-Type: application/json'' \
--header ''api_key: xxxxnnnn-nnxx-xxxn-nnnx-xxxxxxnnnnnn'' \
--data-raw ''{
"reqid": "1",
"org": "somepay",
"ts": "2021-10-05T07:43:13.500+05:30",
"txn": {
"ts": "2021-10-05T07:43:13.500+05:30",…
c. Security
Security protocol between Client Systems and Drona Pay systems can
be altered as the infrastructure and deployment demands. One of
the simplest ways to integrate our systems is to whitelist IP
addresses and Pin SSL Certificates on both sides.
Certificates of Client systems are pinned by us only if events are
to be delivered via webhooks.
6 |','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "API Masters & BNPL", "Page ID": 6, "Version": 6, "iTenantID": 17}');
