1.8.3 Score Response – Parameters
Parameter Type Description
reqid String Score Request ID (Echo back, Case
Sensitive)
org String Organization that created this transaction
(Echo back)
ts String Response Timestamp (ISO-8601 with fractions
and timezone) e.g.
2021-05-26T19:46:24.000+05:30
txn.id String Transaction ID (Echo back, Case Sensitive)
status String Success/Failed (Green/Red)
msg String Remark in case of rule breach / failed
transaction
score.score String Risk score value between 0 and 100. Max of
the scores obtained in all rules
score.decisiondetai
ls
Array Array of Rule name, score obtained (in case
of rule breach), remark for the rule if any
score.decisiondetai
ls.rulename
String Name of the rule
score.decision
details.remarks
String Remarks if any, in case of rule breach or
failure
score.decisiondetai
ls.ruleversion
String Version of the rule currently active
score.decisiondetai
ls.score
Integer Score if any, in case of rule breach or
failure
1.9 Score Response Delivery Options
Depending on Integration demands, Score Responses/Notifications
can be received in following ways.
1.9.1 Synchronous response to POST request
Self explanatory.
1.9.2 Async Score Notification via Websocket
endpoint: /score/events
protocol: STOMP over Websockets (ws)
stomp channel: /topic/score
