The transaction profile consists of all the previous and
subsequent transactions with respect to the selected transaction’s
account address. Default load opens this detail for the most
recent transaction evaluated. Additionally, one can access this
dashboard from the live transaction dashboard by clicking on
UniqueID.
2.4 Data Analyzer
The data analyzer further includes various kinds of dashboard
reports under it, which can be used for investigative analysis for
a longer date range ( beyond present day and the day before). The
data across all the dashboards are mainly filtered on the basis of
date range/ account or VPA address/ class/ decision/rule etc.
To view any of the dashboard tables under the data analyzer, click
on the drop down list for Dashboards and further provide all the
necessary details (Date Range, Level, Type, Address)which are
different depending on the type of dashboard the user wants to
view. The various kinds of table dashboards included under it are
as follows:
2.4.1 Transaction
The Transaction dashboard is used to filter transactions for
a particular account/VPA and a date range. It shows all the
transaction details (inputs, aggregations as well as
evaluated response) that are associated with that particular
account/vpa address for the date range selected
8 |','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "User Manual", "Page ID": 8, "Version": 1, "iTenantID": 17}');
