at every item. the result will be 2667 In our case; we are using the "reduce" operation with empty brackets, indicating that our "accumulator" is an empty array. We are populating that array by using the "merge" command on every mcc code ("current.mcc") inside the array of objects. VIII. kmApart Operator This function is a custom function developed to understand distance in Kms between two strings that are comma separated with latitude and longitude information given. This function uses the Haversine function to calculate the distance Usage: { ">": [ { "kmApart": [ { "var": "txn.attribs.device.geocode" }, { "var": "observations.last_known_location" } ] }, 1 ] } Best Practices ● Rule Param Null Checks to be added in first IF: o Incorporated rule params null checks in the first IF statement for all rules. This ensures that the null checks are performed early in the process, catching any errors promptly. ● Rule Param Null Checks - Provide Error in Config Remarks: o Added error remarks in the False block for all rule params null checks. This helps in identifying and troubleshooting any issues related to the absence of rule','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "Rule Doc", "Page ID": 42, "Version": 5, "iTenantID": 17}');
