1.5.2 Account Events API – Charge Dispute Example
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
{
"externalId": "kdfc-asif-ncjs-dslk",
"eventType": "CRM-CHARGE-DISPUTE",
"eventTime": "2021-09-30T10:30:45.000+05:30",
"eventRemark": "overseas charge",
"eventAmount": 500000,
"attribs": {
"crm-ref": "eifo-asif-ncjs-dslk"
}
}
1.5.3 Account Events API – Parameters
Parameter Type Description
externalId String External ID of event (Case Sensitive) e.g.
payin-20220301-1;
eventType String Type of event e.g.
FRAUD|DISPUTE|CHARGEBACK|SETTLEMENT|PA
YMENTDELAY
eventTime String Timestamp of event entry (ISO-8601 with
fractions and timezone) e.g.
2021-05-26T19:46:24.000+05:30
eventRemark String Remark or additional details about the
event
eventAmount String Amount involved e.g. 5000000
attribs.billing-cyc
le-ending
String Last day of the billing cycle for which
bill was raised and this payment was
received
attribs.crm-ref String Reference ID
1.6 Credit Limit API
Credit Limit API is used to compute the credit limit of an
Account.
Example JSON input message structures for obtaining the credit
limit of an Account is given below:
1.6.1 Credit Limit API – Example
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
{
"reqid": "1",
"org": "somepay",
"ts": "2021-10-05T07:57:13.500+05:30",
"creditlimit": {
"externalId": "a03",
"accountType": 1,
77 |','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "API Masters & BNPL", "Page ID": 77, "Version": 6, "iTenantID": 17}');
