● A simulation can have multiple runs. Each run needs a run ID,
a date range, and modified rule detail/rule parameters
● For each successful run, a separate table is created in the
Simulations schema with the SimID + Run ID naming convention.
This shows results of original rule score vs simulated run
score against each txn ID within date range of run
● When we create Simulation it is saved in the sim schema under
‘simulations’ table. It will show how many simulations were
created.
● When we run a simulation, it is saved in the sim schema under
the ‘run’ table. Once run triggers it saves all information
in the run table like runid, simid, date range, vcruledetail,
vcruleparams, transaction count, created date and itenantid.
● Once Run triggers, it will create one new table called
‘simid_runid’. It will display the same entries which are
mentioned as transaction count in the run table along with
default and changed threshold. This will display simulations
considered or not.
● Endpoint to run a simulation is as given below
POST: {{base_url}}/sim/run/{{simID}}
1.15.12 Run Simulation Prerequisites
For creating a Simulation, a pre-request script has to define the
SIM name for the simulation to be created.
