level of the transaction, the rule(s) triggered, the
transaction parties (payer, payee) and amount.It also
consists of a Dashboard section presenting all the
information relating to the payer or payee transactions.
There are toggle buttons for both payer and payee for
switching between account or VPA level filtering. There
are links under them which redirect to the transaction
profile and party profile section under the data
analyzer dashboard tab.
● Transactions tab: It details all the information
relating to the original transaction as well as computed
parameters:
○ Org: Organization associated with the transaction.
○ Ts: The transaction date and time
○ ReqId:unique UD allocated to the transaction
○ Txn: Summarized view of the transaction
○ Payer/payee: All the payer/payee details like
address, amount transferred, currency and type.
○ Observation: real time aggregations used in the
rules
● History tab:It is an audit trail tracking the lifecycle
of the case in chronological order. These include
addition of any comments, attachments and whether the
case was claimed or unclaimed, status changes,
reassignments etc.
● Related Cases tab: Displays all the cases related to the
selected case in the last 2-30 day time frame. Again,
the information can be previewed as deemed by the user,
making use of the filters.
● Master Data tab:Data related to customer account or
payment details are displayed here for ready reference.
● Profile Tab : Data related to the historical aggregates
for the Payer/Payee involved in the transaction appear
here, with 5 to 6 key aggregates needed.
3.2 Case Summary
Case summary details the cases with status as on date. Following
filters need to be applied to extract information:
● Case Type: where all the cases can be selected or specific
case types like Merchant Risk Score, Double Debit, Declined
Transactions etc
● Date Range: The required date range
● Status: Either claimed or unclaimed
