> `[DELETE /accounts/{id}]` to soft delete an account
> `[GET /accounts/{id}]` to fetch an account record
1.3.1 Accounts API – Example
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
{
"externalId": "a03",
"accountType": 1,
"accountNumber": "00123456790",
"ifsc": "HDFC0000002",
"onboarding_date": "2021-09-30T12:00:00",
"merchant": false,
"verified": true,
"attribs": {
"HNI": true,
"CORPORATE": true
},
"account_categories": [
"classic",
"salary"
]
"record_Status": 0
}
1.3.2 Accounts API – Parameters
Parameter Type Description
externalId* String account ID in external system (Unique &
Case Sensitive) e.g. 12121 or c04
Specifications - Min length = 3, Max length
= 100, Unique, Cannot be NULL, Cannot be
Updated
accountType Integer Account Type
accountNumber String Account Number
ifsc String IFSC code
onboarding_date String Timestamp of onboarding of the accounte.g.
2020-01-13T12:00:00
Specifications - onboarding date time as
local ISO8601 format
i.e. `yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ss`
merchant Bit Whether customer is a merchant or not e.g.
TRUE|FALSE
verified Bit Whether customer is verified or not e.g.
TRUE|FALSE
attribs String Additional attributes as given below
Specification - Max length = 2048
attribs.HNI String Attribute to identify whether the customer
is below the HNI segment. These are custom
attributes defined at time of
implementation
account_categories String Category of account e.g.
Classic|Salary|UMC|Yrs10+
record_Status Integer Value set to 0 for create and update. Value
set to 1 for delete.
12 |','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "API Masters & BNPL", "Page ID": 12, "Version": 6, "iTenantID": 17}');
