 complete picture of customer activity. This can include transfers, deposits, and withdrawals. ● Rules in transaction monitoring / fraud detections are logical checks or sets of conditions that help you decide if an activity is fraudulent or not. ● For e.g., Let’s assume, you know that a payment address belongs to a fraudster and needs to be blacklisted (blocked). Therefore, the most basic type of rule base on if/else logic could be: if payment address = deena@oksbi, then block transaction 11. Categorization of Rules in Drona Pay ● CATEGORY - Transaction ● MODE - Static/Dynamic ● SIDE - Payer/Payee/Both ● DIMENSION - Value based, Count based, IP based/ MCC Based/ Location based ● Batch - Daily batch, Weekly batch, Monthly batch','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "Rule Doc", "Page ID": 1, "Version": 5, "iTenantID": 17}');
