1.1.3 Decision API - Parameters
Parameter Type Description
productId* Integer Internal Id associated with the Product
for which the decision is being created
decisionName* String Name of the Decision as per internal
reference
decisionDetail String Detail regarding the decision, if any
decisionMapInfo String
active* Boolean Whether the decision is active i.e.
currently in use e.g. TRUE | FALSE
record_status Integer Value set to 0 for create and update.
Value set to 1 for delete.
resultParams jsonb Stores criteria in JSON format to
configure scoring aggregations and to map
workflows for specified score ranges
resultParams.action array
of
objects
Stores the action for each criteria and
define the decisioning logic depending on
score or amount to perform when the
transaction triggered
resultParms.action.r
ule
json Defines the jsonlogic/ rule criteria to
pick the action applicable. for eg:
{"rule": { "and": [ { ">": [ { "var":
"finalscore" }, 50 ] } ] }}
resultParams.action.
status
str Status of the transaction to be set based
on the decisioning logic. Can be
“Success”/ “Failed”.
resultParams.action.
remarks
str remarks of the transaction to be set based
on the decisioning logic
resultParams.action.
bworkflow
boolean Whether workflow is to be invoked or not
based on the decisioning logic. eg true,
false
resultParams.action.
workflow_name
str Workflow name to be invoked based on the
decisioning logic rule. eg
