endpoint: /device/file/{deviceId}
method: POST
header:"Content-Type: multipart/form-data"
curl --location --request POST ''http://HOST:PORT/device/file/d001'' \
--form ''file=@"/mnt/d/filesdir/d001_20220120_101520.zip"'' \
Compressed Files being uploaded should have a unique name. We
recommend using deviceId and an incrementing number.
Format for compressed file in ZIP format.
|-contacts.json
|-calllog.json
|-smslog.json
|-email.json
|-apps.json
|-locationlog.json
json files should contain respective json objects, along with
mandatory fields as described in the Info API.
e.g.: smslog.json should contain.
{
"deviceId": "d001",
"smslog": [
{
"origin" : "SMSBANK",
"body" : "",
"date_sent": "2021-05-26T19:46:24.000+05:30"
}
]
}
1.14 Device Profile Query API
1.1.1 Device Profile Ready Notification via WebHook
If integration demands delivery of Score Events via WebHook, then
following points are to be considered.
a) Client System will provide an HTTPS POST EndPoint.
b) Drona Pay system will send the above mentioned payload on
that endpoint for each score event.
c) Client System’s Authentication and authorization modes will
have to be agreed at the time of integration. One of the
simplest modes could be to whitelist the IP addresses of
Drona Pay API servers on client’s infrastructure and Drona
Pay can pin the SSL certificate of client systems for all
communications.
1.14.1 Device Profile Ready Notification via WebHook –
Example
method: POST
content-type: application/json
body:
{
"deviceId": "device_001",
