parameters passed to evaluate the rule
logic(stringified). It contains of rule
type (Alert/Block), workflow name, success
score, success remarks, failure score,
failure remarks, rule threshold values
ruleOrder String Stringified JSON for determining rule
sequence.eg"{\"FailedRule\":X,\"SuccessRule\":
X}". For the first rule rule, we use
"{\"FailedRule\":X,\"SuccessRule\":X,
\"StartRule\":1,}"
active Boolean Whether the rule is active i.e. currently
in use e.g. TRUE | FALSE
custom Boolean Whether the rule created is a custom rule
using JSONLogic or has been created using
Python. Currently all rules have the field
populated as TRUE owing to creation using
JSONLogic
label String Stringified JSON Object that shows the
labels for the rule. Labels help in
categorising the rule and used for
filtering the rule on the UI
ruleType String A form of categorization of rule. ENUMs
include - Static, Dynamic, Heuristic and
ML
ruleDimension String A form of categorization of rule. ENUMs
include - Value, Count, List, Velocity
instance Integer Number of instances of the base rule ID
that has been used so far within the
decision to create derived rules. For eg.
2, if 2 new rules map to the same
available ruleID
action String Operation to be performed on the rule.This
field will remain null when we do a GET
“A”- Add
“M” - Modify
“X” - Delete
versionID Integer Version number of the rule. Default value
is null. When a user edits the rule, the
version number is auto-incremented
starting from 0
approvedDateTimeStamp String Timestamp of the approved rule change
after check approval. This is considered
as the timestamp for rule change
1.4 App Events API
User behaviour on the App is collated to develop a behavioural
profile of the user on the App. The API is used to obtain App
telemetry data which is used to construct metrics, events and
traces / journeys performed by the User.
Example JSON input message structure for App Events for a DeviceID
is given below:
