txn, payer, payee) ▪ Profile Computations ▪ Rule processing dictionary [ status, score, workflow, remarks/side , rule-order (in case of Branch rules)] ● Therefore, to fetch the values from any of the above-mentioned so that logical checks/conditions can be evaluated in rule JSON, the correct reference needs to be provided. ● To fetch the required threshold values from rule params, always use the following reference in rule JSON: { "var": "rule_params.values.single_txn_amt_val_threshold" } ● To fetch the required observation values from rule params, use the following reference in rule JSON: { "var": "observations.instructed_amount"','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "Rule Doc", "Page ID": 10, "Version": 5, "iTenantID": 17}');
