If integration demands delivery of Score Events via WebHook, then
following points are to be considered.
a) Client System will provide an HTTPS POST EndPoint.
b) Drona Pay system will send the above mentioned payload on
that endpoint for each score event.
c) Client System’s Authentication and authorization modes will
have to be agreed at the time of integration. One of the
simplest modes could be to whitelist the IP addresses of
Drona Pay API servers on client’s infrastructure and Drona
Pay can pin the SSL certificate of client systems for all
communications.
1.9.4 Async Score Notification via WebHook – Example
endpoint: scorereader.whatbank.com/score/events
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
{
"reqid": "1",
"org": "somepay",
"ts": "2021-10-05T07:57:13.500+05:30",
"txn": {
"id": "t1",
"orgTxnId": "ot1",
},
"status": "Failed",
"score": {
"score": 0.0 }
}
Notes:
● In parameter description tables of relevant APIs, the “*”
denotes ‘Mandatory Parameter’.
● Optional parameters for a record can be entered with ‘NULL’.
● For APIs supporting CRUD instructions, for ‘DELETE’ - sending
payload of the entire record is not required and only DELETE
method called on a given endpoint with {externalId} would
suffice.
f.
g.
