Each case has a case id, case date, risk score of the
particular case and case status. One can use the search bar
to search by case id.
The order/sequence of cases can be changed with the help of
sort direction button in an ascending or descending format,
according to:
● Created Date
● Risk Score
● Transaction Amount
Cases can be filtered further with the help of the filter
icon present right below the search bar. Cases can be
filtered using values like:
● Case Type: Case type typically shows the workflow name
configured for the instance as per score ranges
● Date range: Date range when the case was created
● Status: Review case, review case by DB Team etc.
● Level: Account or VPA.
● Type: Payer, Payee, Both.
● No of Case: 20,30,50. Default load shows 20
● Rule: Rule names viz. Blacklisted Payee, CP key entered
etc.
● Transaction amount: range of transaction amount
● Address: The address associated.
● Risk Score: can be used with ‘>’,’<’,’=’ or combination
of symbols.
