1.6.2 Credit Limit API – Parameters
Parameter Type Description
Reqid String Payment Request ID (Echo back, Case
Sensitive) e.g. 3
Org String Organization that created this transaction
(Echo back)
Timestamp String Error Timestamp (ISO-8601 with fractions
and timezone) e.g.
2021-05-26T19:46:24.000+05:30
creditlimit.externa
lId
String Account ID in external system (Unique &
Case Sensitive) e.g. 12121 or a03
creditlimit.account
Type
String Type of Account : Credit, Loan & PrePaid
creditlimit.account
Number
String Bank account number e.g. 00123456790
1.6.3 Credit Limit Response – Parameters
Parameter Type Description
Reqid String Payment Request ID (Echo back, Case
Sensitive) e.g. 3
Org String Organization that created this transaction
(Echo back)
Timestamp String Error Timestamp (ISO-8601 with fractions
and timezone) e.g.
2021-05-26T19:46:24.000+05:30
Status String Status of transaction e.g. Received|Error
codes
Error String Error Name e.g. Bad Request
Path String Path e.g. /score/submit
1.7 Async Credit Notification API
API will be used for sending back the credit limit for the account
requested through Credit Limit API. Example structure is given
below:
1.7.1 Async Credit Notification API – Example (Credit
Limit Exists)
endpoint: /score/events
protocol: STOMP over Websockets (ws)
stomp channel: /topic/score
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
