Steps to add a Window:
● Click on the “ADD WINDOW” button.
● Once redirected to the Add Window screen Provide with
the unique Window Id, Window Name, Window Duration and a
count for the Window.
● Entering expressions:
○ Select expression: Defines the field that needs to
be aggregated.
○ Where expression: Defines the filter criteria.
○ Group by expression: For payer and payee ID
aggregation, it can be performed on VPA ID and
account ID.
● The changes can be sent for approval (Maker-checker).
5.7 RT Observation
The RT Observation table consists of the following information:
● OBS ID: Unique observation ID.
● NAME: Name of the observation.
● DURATION: P1D,PT15M,PT5M etc.
● REMARKS: Remarks associated with created observation.
● STATUS: Approved/Rejected.
● LAST UPDATE: Last update date and time of the
observation.
● ACTION: View or delete.
