Payment address information can be stored via Standalone VPA API,
where only the payment address of the customer is of relevance in
the context of evaluating transactions / events. For use cases
like Payment processor and Card issuer the Standalone VPA will
suffice.
The risk scoring system also has a three level hierarchy for
storing Customer, Account and Payment Address information and
their mapping, where relevant. For use cases like netbanking and
mobile banking or apps with different products the three level
hierarchy is used.
● Customer data covers the customer information including basic
identity, KYC IDs, Address etc.
o Account data covers information on different types of
accounts like Savings, Current, Credit, Prepaid and
Loan.
▪ Payment address data covers identifiers for each
type of payment instrument like NEFT, RTGS, UPI,
IMPS, and Card.
For e.g. A customer having Savings, Loan and Prepaid accounts can
have multiple Payment addresses for different types of instruments
or products like NEFT, UPI and IMPS as represented below.
Customer: CUST8234
Account: Savings, Loan, Prepaid
Payment Address: Savings Account
NEFT - ADF00092349|08349739874893
UPI - smg@adf
IMPS - 3484923842384902384
Events with regards to a Customer, Account or Payment Address can
be updated to the system through the Account Events API.
1.1 Standalone Payment Address API
Payment-address can be created without mapping it to an account or
a customer. Endpoint and Example Below:
> `[POST /payment_addresses]` to add a standalone payment address
> `[PUT /payment_addresses/{id}]` to update a payment address
> `[DELETE /payment_addresses/{id}]` to soft-delete a payment address
> `[GET /payment_addresses/{id}]` to fetch a payment address record
1.1.1 Standalone Payment Address API – Example (Person)
