charge-back, CUB risk notification, declined
transactions etc
● Date range: Selected date range
● Status: Either claimed or unclaimed
All the information associated with the Decision made are
presented to us including stage of the case, its alert type,
name of the player, payee details and the details related to
the claim made (Claimed by, claimed on)etc.
4. Tryout
The Tryout Section is for the user to run simulations and perform
investigative analysis on the same. The performance of decisions
and the rules associated with them can be checked by creating a
new simulation or testing the previously created ones by making
changes to their threshold values/ the rule in itself.
4.1 Run Simulation
In this section of the Tryout tab all the previously created
simulations can be run with the preset values for threshold limits
or they can be altered to see if there are any changes. On the RHS
