Pay for tracking all the transactions.
● UniqueID: A unique identifier of the transaction that is
hyperlinked. Clicking on the unique ID in the column
redirects the user to the Transaction Profile section of
the Analytics tab.
● Class: Identifier present in the incoming transaction to
recognise and map to the applicable decisioning ruleset.
● Type: Indicates the type of transaction that has
occurred [Account to Party(A2P),Party to Account(P2A),
Account to Account (A2A) etc. Account refers to the
onboarded entity
● Time: The instance at which the transaction had
occurred.
● Amount: Transaction Amount in INR
● Score: Risk score of the transaction, as evaluated by
Drona Pay. This value is in the range (0,100).
● FRMPass: It presents with two values (pass,fail), basis
risk score calculated. Fail indicates real-time block
while Pass indicates an approval by Drona Pay
● Payer Account: Payer account address
● PayerVPA: Virtual payment address of the payer.
● Payee Account: Payee account address
● PayeeVPA: Virtual payment address of the payee.
● PayerName: Payer’s name.
● PayeeName: Payee’s name.
● decisiondetails: Consists of all the rules that were
checked for a particular transaction.
The columns are common across various other dashboard tables
under this section.All the Payer Account, PayerVPA, Payee
Account, PayeeVPA, PayerName, PayeeName redirect to the party
dashboard if clicked onto. The transaction summary can be
viewed for the same at an account or a VPA level.
2.1.3 Decision Details table
On clicking each transaction entry, details of the
transaction for the score allotted are displayed. The columns
are:
● Rule Name: Indicate rules that were evaluated for the
transaction selected
● Score: Respective score associated with every rule
evaluated
● Order: Priority sequence of the rule execution
● Remarks: remarks pertaining to the triggered rule
6 |','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "User Manual", "Page ID": 6, "Version": 1, "iTenantID": 17}');
