It gives an output of all the Rules that were triggered for a
specific date range, helps the user evaluate effectiveness of
the rules and can be used for optimizing the risk strategy.
The dashboard consists of useful fields such as:
● Rule Triggered Count: Trigger count for the rule.
● Total Txn Count: Total number of transactions for which
the rule was considered.
● Rule Efficiency(%): Rule Triggered Count/Total Txn Count
● False Alert %: Denotes the False alert created by the
● Avg Value(Total Txns): Average value of the total
transaction for which the rule was considered.
● Avg Value (Rules Triggered): Average value of the
transactions for which the rules were triggered.
● Rule Id: Denotes the rule id.
9 |','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "User Manual", "Page ID": 9, "Version": 1, "iTenantID": 17}');
