mobilenum String Mobile Number e.g. +91.99999.99999
imei1 String IMEI no. of device e.g. 12345678yui3
imei2 String IMEI no. of device e.g. 12345678yui3
Adid String user-resettable ID for advertising
accountid String Account ID against which advertising id is
mapped
Make String Device manufacturer e.g. Samsung, LG
Model String Model no. of the device e.g. SM-G925P
manufacture_date String Timestamp of device manufacture
date(ISO-8601 with fractions and timezone)
e.g. 2021-05-26T19:46:24.000+05:30
version.osversion String OS version of the device e.g. Android 4
version.date String Timestamp of the current os version
date(ISO-8601 with fractions and timezone)
e.g. 2021-05-26T19:46:24.000+05:30
1.12 Link Device to User API
Link Device to User API is used to link a device to a user at
Customer or Account or Payment Address level. The mapping of which
level is decided at time of implementation based on the nature of
the product and its rules.
1.12.1 Link Device to User API – Example
endpoint: /device/link
method: POST
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
{
"deviceId": "d001",
"mappingLevel": "CUSTOMER|ACCOUNT|VPA",
"entityId": "c04",
}
1.12.2 Link Device to User API – Parameters
Parameter Type Description
deviceid* String Terminal ID of the device as per NPCI or
ISO 20022 (Device ID as created in the
system)
mapinglevel String Device and User Mapping Level e.g.
Customer|Account|Payment_Address
entityId String External id of Customer/Account/VPA
1.13 Device Info API
Device Info API is used to intimate the system of information
obtained from new installs or newly on boarded users as well as
for ongoing users during app interactions. The API is called at
time of
k. On boarding – To assist in risk scoring for new customer
l. App usage – This is to keep system updated on changes in
device and facilitate transaction risk scoring and updates to
credit risk score
92 |','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "API Masters & BNPL", "Page ID": 92, "Version": 6, "iTenantID": 17}');
