The Party Profile dashboard displays the historical computed
parameters available for a particular account/vpa as on a
particular date/date range. All historical aggregations are
computed EOD and are available for usage in rule processing.
The Party Profile aggregations can be configured from the
Historical Profile tab of the Master Menu tab. Few such
parameters have been enlisted below:
● Total Count_Payee/Total Count_Payer: Total transactions
as a payer or a payee. similarly total count for30 days
etc
● Dormant Days_Payer/Dormant Days_Payee: Dormant days for
payer or payee
● Max Value_P1_Payee/Max Value_P1_Payer: Max value for the
last 1 day for Payer or Payee. similarly for 90,45 days
etc
● Avg Value_P90_Payer/Avg Value_P90_Payee: Average value
for the last 90 days as a Payer or Payee.
● Total Value_P7_Payee/Total Value_P7_Payer: Total value
as a Payer/Payee for the last 7 days. Similarly for
15,30,all days etc.
● Active Days_P30_Payee/Active Days_P30_Payer: Active days
as a Payer/Payee for the last 30 days.
● Last Trans Date_Payee/Last Trans Date_Payer: Last
Transaction date as a Payer/Payee.
● First Trans Date_Payee/First Trans Date_Payer: First
Transaction date as a Payer/Payee.
11 |','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "User Manual", "Page ID": 11, "Version": 1, "iTenantID": 17}');
