The party dashboard helps the user to view information in a
summarized format of the data related to the payer or the payee
for the last 2 days. Currently, we can view up to 1000 Txns for
the address. Default load opens the details for the account on the
payer side of the latest transaction evaluated. In addition to the
tables representing transactions and the decision details, there
is a Transaction Summary table and a filter.
The Transaction Summary table consists of transaction count and
sum of transactions that took place in the last two days and
whether they passed or failed for the account.
