11|IOS12|Windows
payee.attribs.device
.app
String App used by the party to do this
transaction e.g. Gpay|PhonePe
1.7 Acknowledgement for Async Score Request
Acknowledgement will be sent for score requests initiated through
Async API.
Example and Json structure are given below:
1.7.1 Ack for Async Request (Transaction Pass)
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
{
"reqid": "29",
"org": "somepay",
"status": "RCVD"
}
1.7.2 Ack for Async Request (Transaction Error)
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
{
"reqid": "29",
"org": "somepay",
"timestamp": "2021-10-19T04:56:20.581+00:00",
"status": 400,
"error": "Bad Request",
"path": "/score/submit"
}
1.7.3 Ack – Parameters
Parameter Type Description
reqid String Score Request ID (Echo back, Case
Sensitive) e.g. 3
org String Organization that created this transaction
(Echo back)
timestamp String Error Timestamp (ISO-8601 with fractions
and timezone) e.g.
2021-05-26T19:46:24.000+05:30
status String Status of transaction e.g. Received|Error
codes
error String Error Name e.g. Bad Request
path String Path e.g. /score/submit
1.8 Score Response
API will be used for sending back the score of transactions
initiated through Score Request API.
Depending on integration choices Score Responses will arrive in
one of the three ways.
a. as response to POST request on /score
b. as a message over websocket connection on /score/events
c. as a POST call to a webhook endpoint in client system
Example structure is given below:
