combination of groups
6.2 Email Scheduler
The Email Scheduler functionality can be used to schedule reports
to be sent to users or emailIDs at a regular interval. All the
reports available in the UI can be scheduled using this
functionality.
6.2.1 Creating a Email Schedule
Steps to create a new email schedule:
● Click on the “CREATE NEW SCHEDULE” button.
● Choose the report that you want to schedule using the Menu,
Sub Menu and Report fields
● Choose a Frequency at which you would want to receive this
report by choosing Frequency, Day and Time
● In case of Weekly and Monthly, choose a Day when you want to
receive the report. In case of Weekly, Day should be between
0 to 7 and in case of Monthly, Day should be between 0 to 30
● Users who need to be added to the schedule can be selected
from dropdown or a custom email id can be added by “ADD
CUSTOM EMAIL” button
● Under the Attribs section all the mandatory fields need to be
filled as per selected report. Period field needs to have the
negative value of number of days for which you want the
report from today for eg. -1 if you want the report of date =
yesterday
● Example screenshot can be seen below,
41 |','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "User Manual", "Page ID": 41, "Version": 1, "iTenantID": 17}');
