 ● The var_array operator is a function in JSONlogic that allows us to fetch specific value from a dictionary key contained within an array. Syntax: var_array(data_array,array_position,key) o data_array: Refers to the array where your data is stored o array_position: Specifies the position of the dictionary within the array, from which the key-value pair is to be examined and retrieved. o key: The name of the key which needs to be fetched Example 1: { "var_array": [','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "Rule Doc", "Page ID": 27, "Version": 5, "iTenantID": 17}');
