setting alternative decision IDs for the
class in consideration
1.3 Rule API
Rules are configured for every decision. List of rules configured
including the sequence and details for every rule can be fetched
using the Rule API.
The API supports CRUD operations and the details on the same is
given below:
> `[POST /arb/{{rules-topic}}_{{itenantid}}/iruleid]` to add/edit/delete a specific
rule for a decision ID
> `[GET /api/v1/testing/rule-configurator/get-rule/idecisionId]` to fetch all rules
for a decision ID
1.3.1 Create Rule API - Example
{
"mst_type": "rules",
"vcrulename": "Suspicious Multiple International card transactions for low values",
"idecisionid": 1060,
"vcruledescription": "International card used for multiple low value transactions",
"vcruledetail":
