Parameter Type Description
timestamp DateTime Timestamp of request submission
status Integer Status of request submitted e.g. 200 |
400 | 500
message String Message of whether the request was
successfully submitted or not based on
the status code of response
1.5.5 Simple Customers API - Unified call to create hierarchy
The Simple Customers API is the lazy API for a single Customer
single Account + single VPA creation in one unified API call. This
is useful when client systems want the flexibility to call a
composite API, however the flipside is that we cannot create
multiple accounts/VPAs for the customer. This is more suitable
when there is no requirement for multiple account/VPA linkage
Endpoint for Simple Customer:
[POST / {{base_url}}/simple_customers]` to add a simple customer
> `[PATCH/simple_customers/{id}]` to update specific record(s) for simple customer
> `[DELETE /simple_customers/{id}]` to soft-delete a simple customer
> `[GET /customers/{id}]` to fetch a customer record
