 by each payer/payee identifier. Observation is the query result by applying the appropriate aggregate function for that data-set computed for a time interval and returned for the party as of the current txn ● Observations are thus processed in sequential order of `[ wid, oid]`. ● Observations are added to the object as and when they are computed. Window and Observation Logic can refer to any observation computed before itself. ● Observations are always defined for a subset of the time window (P1D/P2D/PT24H/PT1H/PT2H etc.) that you have previously configured for its associated window ● Under a defined window, the observations can be configured with time frames such as PT5M,PT15M,PT30M,PT60M,PT1H,PT4H i.e ISO 8601 format ● Possible aggregation types are COUNT/COUNT_IF/ SUM, SUM_IF/MAX/AVG/COUNT_UNIQUE/COUNT_ALIKE/LAST_KNOWN. Sample observation: { "observationId": 1, "observationName": "payer_m30_txn_count", "observationDescription": "Count of txns in last 30 mins for a VPA Id as Payer", "windowId": 1,','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "Rule Doc", "Page ID": 7, "Version": 5, "iTenantID": 17}');
