Parameter Type Description
externalId* String Unique External ID of payment address for
the organisation’s identifier (Case
Sensitive)e.g. R0001f12
Specifications - Min length = 3, Max length
= 100, Unique, Cannot be NULL, Cannot be
Updated
payment_address* String Unique payment address of the customer if
different from the organisation’s
identifier e.g. sujoym@okhdfc
Specification - Max length = 255
productid Integer Product to which the payment address is
mapped to e.g. UPI, NEFT, RTGS, CARD
vpaName String Name of the virtual payment account e.g.
Sujoy Mondal
Specification - Max length = 255
onboarding_date String Timestamp of onboarding of the VPAe.g.
2020-01-13T12:00:00
Specifications - onboarding date time as
local ISO8601 format
i.e. `yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ss`
expiry_date String Timestamp of entry expiry (ISO-8601 with
fractions and timezone) e.g.
2021-05-26T19:46:24.000+05:30
Specifications - ISO-8601 Pattern =
yyyy-mm-dd, Timezone = IST
merchant Bit Whether customer is a merchant or not e.g.
TRUE|FALSE
verified Bit Whether customer is verified or not e.g.
TRUE|FALSE
attribs.cash_limit Integer Upper Cash limit set for withdrawal on a
card e.g. 7500000
attribs.credit_limi
t
Integer Monthly expenditure limit for a card e.g.
8000000
vpa_categories String Category of vpa e.g. hi-freq, low-value
record_Status Integer Value set to 0 for create and update. Value
set to 1 for delete.
1.5 PATCH Update
The PATCH request of the API supports update of a particular
customer / account / payment address by only providing the
required fields and not the entire json that is used in PUT
request. Via this request only the supplied fields would be
replaced in the original object. The attribs section of API can be
added / updated / deleted by using the add / replace / remove
functions under attribs. Example of json input structure is given
below:
> `[PATCH /customers/{id}]` to update a specific record(s) for a customer
> `[PATCH /accounts/{id}]` to update a specific record(s) for an account
> `[PATCH /payment_addresses/{id}]` to update a specific record(s) for a payment
address
> `[PATCH /simple_customers/{id}]` to update a specific record(s) for a simple
customer
14 |','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "API Masters & BNPL", "Page ID": 14, "Version": 6, "iTenantID": 17}');
