This dashboard displays all the information about the rules
triggered on an account-wise basis and the filters help with
the in-depth extraction of information by entering date
range, class, decision, and rule values.
The table presented displays all the information pertaining
to the account; like the transaction date time, transaction
class, the decision with the respective account, rule and
score information along with payer and payee account and VPA
IDs.
2.4.4 Master Extracts
Master Data relating to payments is stored in a hierarchical
format for several different use cases like netbanking,
mobile banking etc.Levels in the hierarchy include Customer
data, account data and VPA data.
● Customer Data: It’s the first level of hierarchy and
consists of all the customer level information
consisting of address, KYC IDs etc
● Account Data: It’s the second level of hierarchy and
denotes the type of account, example savings account,
current account, prepaid etc linked to a customer.
● VPA Data:It’s the third level of hierarchy and includes
information about the payment instrument used for the
transaction linked to a particular account.
Alternatively, it also includes stand alone payment
addresses onboarded without linkage to accounts/customer
Once the Master Extracts dashboard is selected the user can
select the level for which they want to preview the data,
consisting of Customer, Account and VPA.
