1.8 Device Fingerprint API
Device fingerprint obtained and parameters captured when a user
logs in from a particular device is given below. The response
compares values obtained during current login with historic values
and provides a score that determines the extent of mismatch (if
any) between the login instances of the user.
1.8.1 Device Fingerprint API - Example (Browser)
endpoint:/api/v1/device/fingerprint
method: POST
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
{
"reqId": 1650445549028,
"reqTs": "2022-04-20T14:35:49+05:30",
"behaviourId": "pallavi",
"identity": {
"customer_id": "pallavi"
},
"fingerprint": {
"audio": 124.04347527516074,
"browser": "chrome",
"cookiesEnabled": true,
"deviceMemory": 8,
"hardwareConcurrency": 8,
"platform": "Win32",
"fontCount": 13,
"fontList": "Calibri, Century, Century Gothic, Franklin Gothic, Leelawadee, MS
Reference Specialty, MS UI Gothic, MT Extra, Marlett, Microsoft Uighur, Monotype
Corsiva, Pristina, Segoe UI Light",
"languages": "en-IN",
"sessionID": "3911163FC451197367BB22F8E0363EEE",
"screenResolution": "864, 1536",
"screenColorDepth": 24,
"timezone": "Asia/Calcutta",
"touchSupport": false,
"pluginCount": 5,
"pluginList": "PDF Viewer, Chrome PDF Viewer, Chromium PDF Viewer, Microsoft Edge
PDF Viewer, WebKit built-in PDF"
}
}
1.8.2 Device Fingerprint API - Parameters (Browser)
Parameter Type Description
reqId String Request ID of the session
reqTs Date
Time
Login timestamp
behaviourId String ID of the customer (in case different
from customer ID)
identity.customer_id String ID of the customer
Fingerprint Array Array of fingerprint parameters that
are captured
fingerprint.platform String Fingerprint platform (browser or
mobile)
