Details on the key parameters (Columns) of the table:
● CASE ID: It displays the case ID and clicking on it redirects
to the Tasks section of the Case Management tab.
● CASE TYPE: Tells about the case type; AML, QC, Blocked
settlements etc
● STAGE: Mentions the stage of the review of the case.
● ALERT SUMMARY: A brief description of the generated alert
● CLAIMED BY: The member user who claimed the case
● CLAIMED ON: Date and time on which the case was claimed
● CREATED DATE and STATUS: current status of the case
The Case Summary can be exported using the export button on the
top right corner under the user profile.
3.3 Reports
Listed below are the key reports related to case management:
3.3.1 Case Status Wise Summary
It displays a status wise summary of cases for a date range:
● Case Type: Displays the Case Type; like AML Cases,
Chargeback, Double Debit etc.
● Created Tickets: Total tickets created for a case
● Open Tickets: Tickets that are currently open
● In Process: No. of tickets under process
● Closed Tickets: No. of tickets that have been closed
20 |','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "User Manual", "Page ID": 20, "Version": 1, "iTenantID": 17}');
