vcruledetail String Stringified JSON Logic
vcruleorder String Stringified JSON for determining rule
order.eg"{\"FailedRule\":X,\"SuccessRule\":X}"
. For the first rule rule, we use
"{\"FailedRule\":X,\"SuccessRule\":X,
\"StartRule\":1,}"
bcustom Boolean Whether the rule created is a custom rule
using JSONLogic or has been created using
Python. Currently all rules have the field
populated as TRUE owing to creation using
JSONLogic
bdelete Boolean Value set to FALSE for Add and Modify
Operation. Value set to TRUE for delete
operation
bactive Boolean Whether the decision is active i.e.
currently in use e.g. TRUE | FALSE
iuserid Integer User ID making the change
action String Operation performed on the rule
eg
“A” - Add
“M” - Modify
“X” - Delete
mst_type String add/edit operations on rules, we need to
add an additional field called "mst_type"
in the arb request. This field should be
“rules”
StartRule Integer 1 if it''s the first rule of the rule
sequence and 2 if not.
Notes:
For the first rule, we specify {“FailedRule":X,"SuccessRule":X,
"StartRule":1}, for the last rule we specify{“FailedRule":
-1,"SuccessRule": -1}, for an alert rule we specify {“FailedRule":
X,"SuccessRule": X},for a block rule we specify {“FailedRule":
-1,"SuccessRule": X} in case of rule order
Starting Rule: Set the StartRule parameter to "1" if the request
involves processing the starting rule.
Other Rules: Set the StartRule parameter to "2" or any integer
greater than 1 if the request involves processing rules other than
the starting rule.
we need to add an additional field called "mst_type" in the arb
request. This field is to be auto populated based on below logic:
POST: {{base_url}}/arb/{{rules_topic}}/{{ruleID}}
Body:
{
"mst_type": "rules",
}
