1.8.7 Device Fingerprint Response - Parameters
Parameter Type Description
Score Integer Score computed on comparing
fingerprint parameters captured on
latest login with historic login
profile
details Array Array of all parameters captured with
‘Bit’ value of TRUE or FALSE based on
comparison of latest vs historic
login sessions. TRUE if parameters
are the same, FALSE if parameters are
different.
1.9 IP Fingerprint API
IP fingerprint obtained when a user logs in from a particular
device is given below. The response compares value obtained during
current login with historic value and provides a score that
determines the extent of mismatch (if any) between the login
instances of the user.
1.9.1 IP Fingerprint API - Example
endpoint:/api/v1/device/ipaddress
method: POST
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
{
"reqId": 1650445549726,
"reqTs": "2022-04-20T14:35:49+05:30",
"behaviourId": "pallavi",
"identity": {
"customer_id": "pallavi"
},
"ip": {
"observed_at": "2022-04-20T14:35:49+05:30",
"addr": "117.215.29.9"
}
}
1.9.2 IP Fingerprint API - Parameters
Parameter Type Description
reqId String Request ID of the session
reqTs Date Time Login timestamp
behaviourId String ID of the customer (in case different
from customer ID)
identity.customer_id String ID of the customer
Ip Array Array of ip parameters that are
captured
