details.longitude String Longitude of observed IP
details.proxy_type String Proxy type details
1.10 KeyStroke Dynamics
Keystroke dynamics or typing biometrics is a behavioural biometric
that refers to the automated method of identifying or confirming
the identity of an individual based on the manner and the rhythm
of typing on a keyboard.
1.10.1 Keystroke Dynamics - Example
endpoint:
method: POST
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
{
"reqId": 1650445549032,
"reqTs": "2022-04-20T14:35:49+05:30",
"behaviourId": "pallavi",
"identity": {
"customer_id": "pallavi"
},
"ksmetric": {
"observed_at": "2022-04-20T14:35:47+05:30",
"element": "password",
"keystrokes":
"0,108,359,466,713,804,1135,1163,1450,1566,1822,1918,2153,2249,2484,2543"
}
}
1.10.2 Keystroke Dynamics - Parameters
Parameter Type Description
reqId String Request ID of the session
reqTs Date Time Login timestamp
behaviourId String ID of the customer (in case different
from customer ID)
identity.customer_id String ID of the customer
Ksmetric Array Array of keystroke metric details
that are captured
ksmetric.observed
_at
Date Time Timestamp of capturing keystroke
metrics
ksmetric.element string Element of which the keystrokes are
captured e.g. password
ksmetric.keystrokes String Keystrokes i.e. time spent on typing
the password
1.10.3 Keystroke Dynamics Response - Example
{
"score": "0.22372977077838843",
"details": {
90 |','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "API Masters & BNPL", "Page ID": 90, "Version": 6, "iTenantID": 17}');
