 comparison: we assess whether the calculated number of milliseconds surpasses the "dayThreshold." In this instance, the threshold is set at 30 days, which is converted into milliseconds using the "days" function. Note: Other supported operations of JSONlogic can be viewed at https://jsonlogic.com/operations.html VI. substr Operator ● The substr operator in JSONlogic allows you to get a portion of a string. ● Give a positive start position to return everything beginning at that index. (Indexes of course start at zero.) Syntax: {"substr": ["STRING" , INDEX]}','{"Date": "2025-03-24", "DocName": "Rule Doc", "Page ID": 37, "Version": 5, "iTenantID": 17}');
