erType": "PERSON", "verifiedName": "Karthik Rajan Nair", "record_status": 0, "identity_type1": "PAN", "identity_type2": "AADHAAR", "onboarding_date": "2024-07-13T00:00:00", "iso_country_code": "IN", "identity_details1": "KARNR4567K", "identity_details2": "verified aadhar", "registered_mobile": "9845098765", "address_geolocation": "12.9279,77.6271"}, "merchant": true, "verified": true, "accountId": 57990, "itenantid": 17, "externalId": "BlrBizOwner38", "accountName": "Karthik Nair", "accountType": 1, "default_mcc": 7399, "expiry_date": null, "accountNumber": "700942186500", "record_status": 0, "accountProvider": "Axis Bank", "onboarding_date": "2024-07-13T10:30:00.000"}','This case can be reasonably ignored. The merchant, a proprietary business owner from Bangalore onboarded in July 2024, made two high-value transactions totaling ₹605,000 on the same day. While this represents a 303% increase from the prior average monthly value (₹150,000), and transaction count temporarily spiked from an average of 4 to 2 in a single day, the amounts (₹300,000 and ₹305,000) are non-round and aligned with business activities (infrastructure and vendor payments). No identical or repetitive patterns were observed, and the account has been active for over 250 days with full KYC. Given the context and nature of the payments, the case appears normal and does not warrant further investigation.','False Positive',17,'93e20b4d-1ffb-44ea-b0ed-d9e10293eb5d');
