INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('API Masters & BNPL',6,'2025-03-24',5,'a. Introduction
Drona Pay helps financial institutions mitigate risk in Payments
and Lending. We support a range of products including Credit Card,
Debit Card, BNPL, UPI, NEFT & IMPS. The channels for the
transactions include APIs, Payment gateways, Net banking & Mobile
banking apps. We cover transactional risk scoring in real time
use cases for Banks, BNPL, Payment processors and FinTechs.
The high level implementation follows two models: Bank and FinTech
(PSP, BNPL, Wallet etc.). In the Bank implementation model the
Drona Pay Risk Scoring solution interfaces with the Switch/Gateway
(UPI, NEFT, CC, RTGS etc.). The Switch / Gateway will send payment
requests to both FRM and Core Banking/ Limit validation systems.
If both systems approve of the transaction the same will be
approved by the Switch.
Fig 1: Bank Implementation Model
In the FinTech implementation model the processing engine for the
products like payment or wallet or BNPL will interface with Drona
Pay and send messages for risk scoring.
5 |',17,'f37a5cdd-1966-49a3-b758-392c485d9bb1');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('API Masters & BNPL',6,'2025-03-24',6,'Fig 2: FinTech (PSP, BNPL) Implementation Model
The Score Request, Score Response & Score Events API Flow are
depicted below and form the bulk of the communication with the
Drona Pay Risk Scoring system.
Score Events can also be delivered via a webhook, if the
deployment requires it.
b. Authentication
When you are ready to start the risk scoring process, send us an
email and we will send you test credentials. Your email should
include the IP address from which the score requests will be
initiated (this IP Address will be whitelisted on our server). We
will provide the API key and the URL. When you initiate any API
call, you will need to pass the key in the header, as shown below:
curl -X request POST \
https://testscore.dronapay.com/score \
--header ''Content-Type: application/json'' \
--header ''api_key: xxxxnnnn-nnxx-xxxn-nnnx-xxxxxxnnnnnn'' \
--data-raw ''{
"reqid": "1",
"org": "somepay",
"ts": "2021-10-05T07:43:13.500+05:30",
"txn": {
"ts": "2021-10-05T07:43:13.500+05:30",…
c. Security
Security protocol between Client Systems and Drona Pay systems can
be altered as the infrastructure and deployment demands. One of
the simplest ways to integrate our systems is to whitelist IP
addresses and Pin SSL Certificates on both sides.
Certificates of Client systems are pinned by us only if events are
to be delivered via webhooks.
6 |',17,'0a0dd566-3d3e-4ddc-b345-3d5c5621f4bf');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('API Masters & BNPL',6,'2025-03-24',7,'d. Master Data Overview
Payment address information can be stored via Standalone VPA API,
where only the payment address of the customer is of relevance in
the context of evaluating transactions / events. For use cases
like Payment processor and Card issuer the Standalone VPA will
suffice.
The risk scoring system also has a three level hierarchy for
storing Customer, Account and Payment Address information and
their mapping, where relevant. For use cases like netbanking and
mobile banking or apps with different products the three level
hierarchy is used.
● Customer data covers the customer information including basic
identity, KYC IDs, Address etc.
o Account data covers information on different types of
accounts like Savings, Current, Credit, Prepaid and
Loan.
▪ Payment address data covers identifiers for each
type of payment instrument like NEFT, RTGS, UPI,
IMPS, and Card.
For e.g. A customer having Savings, Loan and Prepaid accounts can
have multiple Payment addresses for different types of instruments
or products like NEFT, UPI and IMPS as represented below.
Customer: CUST8234
Account: Savings, Loan, Prepaid
Payment Address: Savings Account
NEFT - ADF00092349|08349739874893
UPI - smg@adf
IMPS - 3484923842384902384
Events with regards to a Customer, Account or Payment Address can
be updated to the system through the Account Events API.
1.1 Standalone Payment Address API
Payment-address can be created without mapping it to an account or
a customer. Endpoint and Example Below:
> `[POST /payment_addresses]` to add a standalone payment address
> `[PUT /payment_addresses/{id}]` to update a payment address
> `[DELETE /payment_addresses/{id}]` to soft-delete a payment address
> `[GET /payment_addresses/{id}]` to fetch a payment address record
1.1.1 Standalone Payment Address API – Example (Person)
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body: {
7 |',17,'61260e99-0b4f-4680-8b53-650c982bca3c');
