1.1.2 Standalone Payment Address API – Example
(Merchant)
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body: {
"externalId": "r000111",
"payment_address": "maplestores@okhdfc",
"vpaName": "Maple Stores",
"onboarding_date": "2020-10-01",
"merchant": true,
"verified": true,
"attribs": {
"ecom": true
}
1.1.3 Standalone Payment Address API – Parameters
Parameter Type Description
externalId* String Unique External ID of payment address
for the organisation’s identifier
(Case Sensitive)e.g. R0001f12
Specifications - Min length = 3, Max
length = 100, Unique, Cannot be NULL,
Cannot be Updated
payment_address String Unique payment address of the customer
if different from the organisation’s
identifier e.g. sujoym@okhdfc
Specification - Max length = 255
vpaName String Name of the virtual payment account
e.g. Sujoy Mondal
Specification - Max length = 200
onboarding_date String Date of onboarding of the customer
e.g. 2020-01-13
Specifications - ISO-8601 Pattern =
yyyy-mm-dd, Timezone = IST
Merchant Bit Whether customer is a merchant or not
e.g. TRUE|FALSE
Verified Bit Whether customer is verified or not
e.g. TRUE|FALSE
attribs.cash_limit Integer Upper Cash limit set for withdrawal on a
card e.g. 7500000 (for person)
attribs.credit_limi
t
Integer Monthly expenditure limit for a card e.g.
8000000 (for person)
attribs.ecom Bit Whether the merchant is an e-commerce
org (for merchant)
8 |',17,'c990135a-37e7-4189-9575-5843971ce377');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('API Masters & BNPL',6,'2025-03-24',9,'1.2 Customers API
Customers API is used to create new Customers. A Customer may have
multiple Accounts for Savings, Current, Credit, Prepaid & Loan.
The API supports CRUD operations and the details on the same are
also given below. Example JSON input message structures for
creating a Customer is given below:
> `[POST /customers]` to add a customer
> `[PUT /customers/{id}]` to update a customer
> `[PATCH /customers/{id}]` to update a specific record(s) for a customer
> `[DELETE /customers/{id}]` to soft-delete a customer
> `[GET /customers/{id}]` to fetch a customer record
1.2.1 Customers API - Example (Person)
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
{
"externalId": "c04",
"customerName": "Sujoy Mondal",
"verifiedName": "Sujoy Mondal",
"customerType": "PERSON",
"salutation": "Mr",
"gender": "M",
"doi_dob": "1973-06-21",
"onboarding_date": "2004-08-01T12:00:00",
"postal_code": "400054",
"email": "sujoy.m@gmail.com",
"registered_mobile": "91845723475812",
"default_mcc": 0,
"identity_type1": "AADHAAR",
"identity_details1": "1234-1234-1234",
