INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('API Masters & BNPL',6,'2025-03-24',13,'1.4 Payment Address API
Payment address data covers identifiers for each type of payment
instrument like NEFT, RTGS, UPI, IMPS, and Card.
The API supports CRUD operations and the details on the same are
also given below. Example JSON input message structures for
creating a payment address is given below:
> `[POST accounts/{id}/payment_addresses]` to add a payment address to an account
> `[PUT /payment_addresses/{id}]` to update a payment address
> `[PATCH /payment_addresses/{id}]` to update a specific record(s) for a payment
address
> `[DELETE /payment_addresses/{id}]` to soft-delete a payment address
> `[GET /payment_addresses/{id}]` to fetch a payment address record
1.4.1 Payment Address API – Example (Person)
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
{
"externalId": "R0001f12",
"payment_address": "Sujoym@okhdfc",
"productId": 1,
"vpaName": "Sujoy Mondal",
"onboarding_date": "2021-10-01T12:00:00",
"expiry_date": "2022-09-30",
"merchant": false,
"verified": true,
"attribs": {
"cash_limit": 7500000,
"credit_limit": 9000000
},
"vpa_categories": [
"hi-freq",
"low-value"
]
"record_Status": 0
}
