List Management API
List Management API is used to add entries to Blacklist, Whitelist
and Greylist and any custom list category. The functionality of
records in each list is as follows:
a. List Type (0)|Blacklist – A record entered in the blacklist
needs to be blocked/rejected e.g. If a Card Number is in
blacklist, transactions for that card will be rejected.
b. List Type(1)|Greylist – A record entered in the Greylist that
needs to be alerted e.g. If an Account Number is in the
greylist, transactions of that VPA will create an alert.
c. List Type (2)|Whitelist – A record entered in the whitelist
needs to bypass the blacklist screening e.g. If a Card Number
is in whitelist, the card number will not be validated
against the blacklist entries. The transaction of the card
could fail or pass based on other rules in the system. Only
the blacklist check will not be performed.
d. Any custom list(>2) - For eg: Risky - A geocode/pin code
entered in the risky list will be compared with incoming
transaction field for geocode/pin code to validate whether
transaction is from a risky location. We can also do this
comparison with master data related fields for
geocode/pincode.
Lists can be of different types of parameters e.g. VPA addresses
of Payer / Payee, Device ID, IP, Mobile Number, IMEI, Email ID
etc. The message structure supports addition of these various
types of entries in the list management master with option of
setting a start date and expiry date, to keep the entry in the
list for a limited period of time. It also allows the addition of
attribs to create multi dimensional list data
Example JSON input message structures for creating a Blacklist
entry is given below:
1.5.7 List Management API – Blacklist Example
