INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('API Masters & BNPL',6,'2025-03-24',24,'e. Risk Scoring APIs
1.6 Score Request API
Score Request API is used to get the risk score of a transaction.
Score Request API will be used for all payment and lending
transactions scoring (UPI: Pay and Collect, Credit Card: Pay,
NEFT: Transfer, BNPL: Lend or Pay etc.). Few examples of transaction
classes currently supported are UPI|API, CARD|API, NEFT|ONLINE, UPI|ONLINE,
CARD|POS, CARD|ONLINE, BNPLUPI|API, IMPS|ONLINE. Any transaction
Reversals and Failures are also communicated to the FRM through
the message structure.
Score API is available in synchronous and asynchronous mode. Based
on the integration selected between systems, client systems can
POST score requests to either of the following Endpoints.
POST request on /score will return the score result as response;
while POST request on /score/submit will acknowledge the receipt
of the request, but the score result will come asynchronously via
websocket or webhook depending on integration choices. Correlation
between request and response can be done via unique "reqid".
Endpoint for POST request for Async score is :/score/submit
Endpoint for POST request for Sync score is :/score
Example JSON input message structures for UPI, NEFT and Card for
Score API is given below:
1.6.1 Score Request – Example UPI
endpoint: /score
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
