1.6.8 Score Request – Example Invoice – Parameters
Parameter Type Description
reqid* String Score Request ID (Unique & Case Sensitive)
e.g. Wrfruf039wdn2wd
Specifications - Min length = 1, Max
length = 100
org* String Organization that created this transaction
ts* String Request Timestamp (ISO-8601 with fractions
and timezone) e.g.
2021-05-26T19:46:01.000+05:30
txn.ts* String Transaction Timestamp (ISO-8601 with
fractions and timezone) e.g.
2021-05-26T19:46:24.000+05:30
txn.id* String Unique identifier of the payment (Unique &
Case Sensitive) e.g. djri5fhdG4kd
Specifications - Min length = 1, Max
length = 100
txn.orgTxnId* String Original Transaction ID, if this
transaction is in relation to another
(Case Sensitive) e.g. Trxn1
txn.note String Transaction note by customer e.g. Rent
payment
txn.type* String Type of the transaction e.g.
PENDING|PAY|REJECT|FAILED
PENDING - for invoices that are pending
for approval
REJECT - for invoices rejected by
counterparty
PAY - for successful invoices after
bidding
FAILED - for invoices that were defaulted
on
txn.class* String Classifier indicating organization code
or payment product or payment channel (to
be mutually decided at the time of
implementation) e.g. INVOICE
txn.attribs Additional Attributes for the transaction.
(Valid attributes listed below)
