1.10 KeyStroke Dynamics
Keystroke dynamics or typing biometrics is a behavioural biometric
that refers to the automated method of identifying or confirming
the identity of an individual based on the manner and the rhythm
of typing on a keyboard.
1.10.1 Keystroke Dynamics - Example
endpoint:
method: POST
header:"Content-Type: application/json"
body:
{
"reqId": 1650445549032,
"reqTs": "2022-04-20T14:35:49+05:30",
"behaviourId": "pallavi",
"identity": {
"customer_id": "pallavi"
},
"ksmetric": {
"observed_at": "2022-04-20T14:35:47+05:30",
"element": "password",
"keystrokes":
"0,108,359,466,713,804,1135,1163,1450,1566,1822,1918,2153,2249,2484,2543"
}
}
