Annexure 4 - Simulator APIs
Simulation feature helps us tune performance of rules.At any point
in time, a simulation can be created for 1 particular rule
corresponding to a decision ID, tenant id, rule details and rule
params. Below is the endpoint to add simulation.
POST: {{base_url}}/sim/{{simID}}
1.15.6 Create Simulation- Pre-Request Script
For creating a Simulation, a pre-request script has to define the
SIM name for the simulation to be created.
pm.environment.set("simID", "Testing");
1.15.7 Simulation - Parameters
Parameter Type Description
note String Simulation note given by customer
idecisionid * Integer decision id of the rule to be
simulated
iruleid * Integer ruleid of the rule to create
simulation
itenantid * Integer tenantid of the client
isbatch String its an boolean value if its a batch
rule then should be true else false
vcruledetail Json ruledetails json of the rule to be
simulated. can be null if not
required. This is shared in case of a
new imaginary rule that does not
exist in the master
vcruleparams Json ruleparams json of the rule to be
simulated. can be null if not
required. This is shared in case of a
new imaginary rule that does not
exist in the master
