INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',3,'1. Introduction
1.1 Background
Drona Pay helps financial institutions mitigate risk in Payments
and Lending. We support a range of products including Credit Card,
Debit Card, BNPL, UPI, NEFT,AEP5S & IMPS. The channels for the
transactions include APIs, Payment gateways, Net banking & Mobile
banking apps. We cover transactional risk scoring in real time
use cases for Banks, BNPL, Payment processors and FinTechs.
The high level implementation follows two models: Bank and FinTech
(PSP, BNPL, Wallet etc.). In the Bank implementation model the
Drona Pay Risk Scoring solution interfaces with the Switch/Gateway
(UPI, NEFT, CC, RTGS etc.). The Switch / Gateway will send payment
requests to both FRM and Core Banking/ Limit validation systems.
If both systems approve of the transaction the same will be
approved by the Switch.
Fig 1: Bank Implementation Model
In the FinTech implementation model the processing engine for the
products like payment or wallet or BNPL will interface with Drona
Pay and send messages for risk scoring.
3 |',17,'d4fa13d4-8816-4363-9c21-b96c90cb8b5e');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',4,'Fig 2: FinTech (PSP, BNPL) Implementation Model
The Score Request, Score Response & Score Events API Flow are
depicted below and form the bulk of the communication with the
Drona Pay Risk Scoring system.
Score Events can also be delivered via a webhook, if the
deployment requires it.
1.2 Product
Drona Pay web user application is integrated with Single Sign On.
Login page needs the user to input his/her credentials and select
SSO Provider to authenticate and access the application.
On logging in, the user is directed to the live transaction
dashboard on default load. On the top middle section, the tenant
logo is visible. On the top right corner, the user can head to
Profile and view/edit profile details or log out.
On hovering to the left bar, the user can see the set of menu tabs
available. The key menu tabs include - Analytics, Case Management,
Admin, Try Out and Masters. Each of these tabs are explained in
this document and can be found in the Table of Contents.
Drona Pay has page wise user level access that is configurable.
All our master forms for configuring the product have a
maker-checker system design with an audit trail.
4 |',17,'92b1e14a-0fa0-49c4-a9d8-dd29b42539c9');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',5,'2. Analytics
This tab on the Menu comprises dashboards (real-time as well as
historic) for investigative analysis. The sub options include
● Transaction DB
● Party Dashboard
● Transaction Profile
● Data Analyzer
Post logging on to the platform we are directed to the Transaction
dashboard by default within the Analytics menu,details of which
are mentioned.
2.1 Transaction DB
The dashboard gets updated real time with key transaction
information and risk score for every transaction that is passed to
Drona Pay for evaluation along with decision details of evaluated
rules and failed rules. On clicking any particular transaction
entry, one can find the details of the decision including rules
evaluated and the rule(s) that failed for the transaction.
2.1.1 Transactions Filter
The filters can be used to view specific information as per
the user’s requirement, with filter options on Class (Txn
Identifier) and Score ( >= X, where X is between 0 to 100)
2.1.2 Parameters for Transaction DB
Details on the key parameters (Columns)of the table include
5 |',17,'11028929-2697-48f5-b4af-a5f05df9f8d1');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',6,'● ILiveMessageID: Internal reference generated by Drona
Pay for tracking all the transactions.
● UniqueID: A unique identifier of the transaction that is
hyperlinked. Clicking on the unique ID in the column
redirects the user to the Transaction Profile section of
the Analytics tab.
● Class: Identifier present in the incoming transaction to
recognise and map to the applicable decisioning ruleset.
● Type: Indicates the type of transaction that has
occurred [Account to Party(A2P),Party to Account(P2A),
Account to Account (A2A) etc. Account refers to the
onboarded entity
● Time: The instance at which the transaction had
occurred.
● Amount: Transaction Amount in INR
● Score: Risk score of the transaction, as evaluated by
Drona Pay. This value is in the range (0,100).
● FRMPass: It presents with two values (pass,fail), basis
risk score calculated. Fail indicates real-time block
while Pass indicates an approval by Drona Pay
● Payer Account: Payer account address
● PayerVPA: Virtual payment address of the payer.
● Payee Account: Payee account address
● PayeeVPA: Virtual payment address of the payee.
● PayerName: Payer’s name.
● PayeeName: Payee’s name.
● decisiondetails: Consists of all the rules that were
checked for a particular transaction.
The columns are common across various other dashboard tables
under this section.All the Payer Account, PayerVPA, Payee
Account, PayeeVPA, PayerName, PayeeName redirect to the party
dashboard if clicked onto. The transaction summary can be
viewed for the same at an account or a VPA level.
2.1.3 Decision Details table
On clicking each transaction entry, details of the
transaction for the score allotted are displayed. The columns
are:
● Rule Name: Indicate rules that were evaluated for the
transaction selected
● Score: Respective score associated with every rule
evaluated
● Order: Priority sequence of the rule execution
● Remarks: remarks pertaining to the triggered rule
6 |',17,'6b7c45b9-735e-44f0-9637-258c460c143a');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',7,'2.2 Party Dashboard
The party dashboard helps the user to view information in a
summarized format of the data related to the payer or the payee
for the last 2 days. Currently, we can view up to 1000 Txns for
the address. Default load opens the details for the account on the
payer side of the latest transaction evaluated. In addition to the
tables representing transactions and the decision details, there
is a Transaction Summary table and a filter.
The Transaction Summary table consists of transaction count and
sum of transactions that took place in the last two days and
whether they passed or failed for the account.
7 |',17,'80ded40b-ead5-4013-9175-bbf937a1081a');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',8,'2.3 Transaction Profile
The transaction profile consists of all the previous and
subsequent transactions with respect to the selected transaction’s
account address. Default load opens this detail for the most
recent transaction evaluated. Additionally, one can access this
dashboard from the live transaction dashboard by clicking on
UniqueID.
2.4 Data Analyzer
The data analyzer further includes various kinds of dashboard
reports under it, which can be used for investigative analysis for
a longer date range ( beyond present day and the day before). The
data across all the dashboards are mainly filtered on the basis of
date range/ account or VPA address/ class/ decision/rule etc.
To view any of the dashboard tables under the data analyzer, click
on the drop down list for Dashboards and further provide all the
necessary details (Date Range, Level, Type, Address)which are
different depending on the type of dashboard the user wants to
view. The various kinds of table dashboards included under it are
as follows:
2.4.1 Transaction
The Transaction dashboard is used to filter transactions for
a particular account/VPA and a date range. It shows all the
transaction details (inputs, aggregations as well as
evaluated response) that are associated with that particular
account/vpa address for the date range selected
8 |',17,'1f3653cb-5509-4e26-9593-5da214fee9de');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',9,'2.4.2 Rule Efficiency Report
It gives an output of all the Rules that were triggered for a
specific date range, helps the user evaluate effectiveness of
the rules and can be used for optimizing the risk strategy.
The dashboard consists of useful fields such as:
● Rule Triggered Count: Trigger count for the rule.
● Total Txn Count: Total number of transactions for which
the rule was considered.
● Rule Efficiency(%): Rule Triggered Count/Total Txn Count
● False Alert %: Denotes the False alert created by the
● Avg Value(Total Txns): Average value of the total
transaction for which the rule was considered.
● Avg Value (Rules Triggered): Average value of the
transactions for which the rules were triggered.
● Rule Id: Denotes the rule id.
9 |',17,'6ddd360d-d0f9-443b-8c24-02bff7e73058');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',10,'2.4.3 Account Wise Rules Triggered
This dashboard displays all the information about the rules
triggered on an account-wise basis and the filters help with
the in-depth extraction of information by entering date
range, class, decision, and rule values.
The table presented displays all the information pertaining
to the account; like the transaction date time, transaction
class, the decision with the respective account, rule and
score information along with payer and payee account and VPA
IDs.
2.4.4 Master Extracts
Master Data relating to payments is stored in a hierarchical
format for several different use cases like netbanking,
mobile banking etc.Levels in the hierarchy include Customer
data, account data and VPA data.
● Customer Data: It’s the first level of hierarchy and
consists of all the customer level information
consisting of address, KYC IDs etc
● Account Data: It’s the second level of hierarchy and
denotes the type of account, example savings account,
current account, prepaid etc linked to a customer.
● VPA Data:It’s the third level of hierarchy and includes
information about the payment instrument used for the
transaction linked to a particular account.
Alternatively, it also includes stand alone payment
addresses onboarded without linkage to accounts/customer
Once the Master Extracts dashboard is selected the user can
select the level for which they want to preview the data,
consisting of Customer, Account and VPA.
10 |',17,'af4509a4-de18-43c8-bcb0-d72f2453da1e');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',11,'2.4.5 Party Profile
The Party Profile dashboard displays the historical computed
parameters available for a particular account/vpa as on a
particular date/date range. All historical aggregations are
computed EOD and are available for usage in rule processing.
The Party Profile aggregations can be configured from the
Historical Profile tab of the Master Menu tab. Few such
parameters have been enlisted below:
● Total Count_Payee/Total Count_Payer: Total transactions
as a payer or a payee. similarly total count for30 days
etc
● Dormant Days_Payer/Dormant Days_Payee: Dormant days for
payer or payee
● Max Value_P1_Payee/Max Value_P1_Payer: Max value for the
last 1 day for Payer or Payee. similarly for 90,45 days
etc
● Avg Value_P90_Payer/Avg Value_P90_Payee: Average value
for the last 90 days as a Payer or Payee.
● Total Value_P7_Payee/Total Value_P7_Payer: Total value
as a Payer/Payee for the last 7 days. Similarly for
15,30,all days etc.
● Active Days_P30_Payee/Active Days_P30_Payer: Active days
as a Payer/Payee for the last 30 days.
● Last Trans Date_Payee/Last Trans Date_Payer: Last
Transaction date as a Payer/Payee.
● First Trans Date_Payee/First Trans Date_Payer: First
Transaction date as a Payer/Payee.
11 |',17,'740a6456-39cd-41a2-932e-f77c05e9b5cb');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',12,'● Days in The System_Payer/Days in The System_Payee: Days
in the system as a payer/Payee.
● TxnScore Count_P30_Payee/TxnScore Count_P30_Payer:
Transaction Count for different scores as Payee/Payer
for the last 30 days.
● Relationships_P30_Payer/Relationships_P30_Payee:
Relationship with payees/Payers as Payer/Payee.
2.5 Dashboard : Additional features
All Drona Pay dashboards have a set of common additional features
that make them configurable, self-serve and easy to use. Listed
below are the key features that make it user-friendly and
valuable.
2.5.1 Personalization- selection, sequencing,addition
Clicking on the downward facing arrow right next to the main
menu , allows the user to make custom datagrid selections.
The user can add additional derived columns to the dashboard
table and also select columns by clicking on the checkbox in
front of each of the column names.Additionally, the user can
resequence the columns by dragging them.The applied selection
can be saved for all users/for currently logged in user.
12 |',17,'1482c63e-d785-407f-ae82-62014f24c139');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',13,'2.5.2 Table Actions
Right clicking anywhere on the the table pops up a list of
actions that can be performed on the table including:
● New Table: It is used to create an untitled table using
the data of the table that is being currently viewed.
● Maximize/Minimize: It is used to increase/decrease the
size of the table.
● Duplicate: A duplicate table is created out of the
selected table.
● Create/Delete Global Filter: Removing the global filter
or creating a new one.
● Reset: All the filters and settings applied are reset
● Export: The table can be exported and saved as local
backup in csv/json format for current view/ unfiltered
view
● Copy: Used for copying all the table dashboard values.
13 |',17,'4ab8d8fc-7ab7-4d4d-b95f-99117c46465f');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',14,'2.5.3 Filtering Options- Group By/Sort By/Where/Split
To use any of the group by, sort by, split by or where
filter, the user can just drag and drop the column headers
from the custom datagrid into any of the fields. Each filter
can be used standalone or coupled with the other filters.
The Where field requires a numeric value to be entered
accordingly, which would fit the desired condition of the
greater than, less than or equal to criteria.
14 |',17,'6ccd1578-dc18-4188-906a-d5ff3c562719');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',15,'3. Case Management
The Case Management handles the life-cycle of a created alert. It
helps with the effective management of the flagged transactions
and the lifecycle associated with them. We use a configurable BPMN
Engine to create and implement the workflow.Multiple workflows can
be configured based on risk score range.Additionally, our
workflows can be integrated with third party APIs to facilitate
communication via Email, Whatsapp, SMS, IVR etc and use it for
taking next set of actions. We also have other features such as
time bound escalations to L2/L3 and auto
allocation/reassignment/bulk closure possible.
The Case Management section has five sub sections
● Tasks
● Case Summary
● Reports
● Auto Allocation User mapping
● Bulk Process
3.1 Tasks
3.1.1 Ticket Carousel
The Queue is the leftmost dropdown under the Tasks section
screen; consisting of recently created tickets or cases.
Following are the types of queues available:
● Open:This shows the unclaimed cases, ready to be
actioned
15 |',17,'11e64bee-698a-4264-89de-7bff1d931399');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',16,'● My:This shows the claimed cases for logged in user
● Aggregated: This shows the aggregated cases per account
● Closed: This shows the closed cases overall
● My Closed:This shows the closed cases for logged in user
Each case has a case id, case date, risk score of the
particular case and case status. One can use the search bar
to search by case id.
The order/sequence of cases can be changed with the help of
sort direction button in an ascending or descending format,
according to:
● Created Date
● Risk Score
● Transaction Amount
Cases can be filtered further with the help of the filter
icon present right below the search bar. Cases can be
filtered using values like:
● Case Type: Case type typically shows the workflow name
configured for the instance as per score ranges
● Date range: Date range when the case was created
● Status: Review case, review case by DB Team etc.
● Level: Account or VPA.
● Type: Payer, Payee, Both.
● No of Case: 20,30,50. Default load shows 20
● Rule: Rule names viz. Blacklisted Payee, CP key entered
etc.
● Transaction amount: range of transaction amount
● Address: The address associated.
● Risk Score: can be used with ‘>’,’<’,’=’ or combination
of symbols.
16 |',17,'576e1bc1-b8fe-4c33-915e-69bbea334095');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',17,'3.1.2 Manage Case
It is the middle panel in the tasks screen. The user can
navigate to the ticket that requires attention in the queue
segment of the screen. Upon selection of the ticket the user
henceforth needs to click on the claim button in the Manage
Case segment. This will cause the ticket to be moved to the
personal “my bucket” section and further the case can be
managed under the “Manage Case” segment.This section is
configured as per the BPMN Decisioning framework of the
workflow and helps the user take next set of actions on case:
● Selecting actions from a specific configured set
pertaining to the chosen case, eg reporting case as
“False Positive”/ “Adding to Whitelist”/”Reporting
Fraud”/”Request Evidence”/ “Release Hold” etc
● Initiating IVR/email/SMS communication basis
requirements
● Adding Comments, remarks and attachments to the case as
required.
The ticket can be further submitted, reassigned to some
other person or unclaimed by the user, by clicking on the
respective buttons present on the top of the middle section
17 |',17,'78aa10e4-adf8-4be6-9c5c-2ae02596db3f');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',18,'In case of IVR/Email/SMS, the phone number/email can be
configured in the user profile section by feeding the number
under the respective fields and saving the changes by
clicking on the “Save” button. i.e In case of IVR, The Number
added will be added as an extension to the IVR and will be
visible in the Manage Case segment.
3.1.3 Analysis Support
The Analysis Support is the rightmost segment on the screen.
It consists of various kinds of tabs under it, providing the
user with all the relevant insights at a glance with regards
to the flagged transaction:
18 |',17,'6f6f9913-565b-457a-9193-8888da6f30e7');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',19,'● Summary tab: It provides information regarding the risk
level of the transaction, the rule(s) triggered, the
transaction parties (payer, payee) and amount.It also
consists of a Dashboard section presenting all the
information relating to the payer or payee transactions.
There are toggle buttons for both payer and payee for
switching between account or VPA level filtering. There
are links under them which redirect to the transaction
profile and party profile section under the data
analyzer dashboard tab.
● Transactions tab: It details all the information
relating to the original transaction as well as computed
parameters:
○ Org: Organization associated with the transaction.
○ Ts: The transaction date and time
○ ReqId:unique UD allocated to the transaction
○ Txn: Summarized view of the transaction
○ Payer/payee: All the payer/payee details like
address, amount transferred, currency and type.
○ Observation: real time aggregations used in the
rules
● History tab:It is an audit trail tracking the lifecycle
of the case in chronological order. These include
addition of any comments, attachments and whether the
case was claimed or unclaimed, status changes,
reassignments etc.
● Related Cases tab: Displays all the cases related to the
selected case in the last 2-30 day time frame. Again,
the information can be previewed as deemed by the user,
making use of the filters.
● Master Data tab:Data related to customer account or
payment details are displayed here for ready reference.
● Profile Tab : Data related to the historical aggregates
for the Payer/Payee involved in the transaction appear
here, with 5 to 6 key aggregates needed.
3.2 Case Summary
Case summary details the cases with status as on date. Following
filters need to be applied to extract information:
● Case Type: where all the cases can be selected or specific
case types like Merchant Risk Score, Double Debit, Declined
Transactions etc
● Date Range: The required date range
● Status: Either claimed or unclaimed
19 |',17,'3307d90b-0b00-4f3f-92fe-8b39859e71e9');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',20,'After entering the above details table is presented to the user.
Details on the key parameters (Columns) of the table:
● CASE ID: It displays the case ID and clicking on it redirects
to the Tasks section of the Case Management tab.
● CASE TYPE: Tells about the case type; AML, QC, Blocked
settlements etc
● STAGE: Mentions the stage of the review of the case.
● ALERT SUMMARY: A brief description of the generated alert
● CLAIMED BY: The member user who claimed the case
● CLAIMED ON: Date and time on which the case was claimed
● CREATED DATE and STATUS: current status of the case
The Case Summary can be exported using the export button on the
top right corner under the user profile.
3.3 Reports
Listed below are the key reports related to case management:
3.3.1 Case Status Wise Summary
It displays a status wise summary of cases for a date range:
● Case Type: Displays the Case Type; like AML Cases,
Chargeback, Double Debit etc.
● Created Tickets: Total tickets created for a case
● Open Tickets: Tickets that are currently open
● In Process: No. of tickets under process
● Closed Tickets: No. of tickets that have been closed
20 |',17,'e5c13ed9-ba79-4446-b87f-f658749d87fd');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',21,'3.3.2 Case Type Wise Summary
Under the Case Type wise summary, details can be viewed for
a specific case type by the user to understand the number of
tickets in different stages of the lifecycle of the workflow
for a specific date range
3.3.3 Pendency Report
The pendency dashboard generates output for all the cases
that haven’t been settled yet. It displays all the users and
the groups associated with the case along with the state of
the user.
21 |',17,'866564e9-6bbb-4922-bca6-b6d34f3b3b02');
