INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',26,'5. Masters
5.1 Introduction
The Masters section of the menu entails all the key elements of
the FRM system. The sections under the Masters tab include: -
● Class
● Decision
● Rules
● List
● RT Window
● RT Observation
● Historic Profile
26 |',17,'442f6942-3449-4ef2-816c-866633586fbb');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',27,'Class is a transaction identifier that links an incoming
transaction to a Decision. Decision is a category for which we can
apply scoring mechanisms, rules, models and workflows.Rules are
set for a particular decision and require transaction parameters,
real-time aggregations as well as historical aggregations. These
can be found in RT Window, RT Observation and Historic Profile.
Combined together, they help in configuring a fraud rules
management system.
All master forms undergo maker checker flow.Through the Maker
profile the user can make changes and create Class, Decisions or
Rules. A remark can be added by the Maker profile user while
sending the change for approval.The Checker is the user who
verifies the changes made by the Maker and can approve/reject the
changes.
5.2 Class Management
Class management involves the identification of the category or
the type of transaction that is captured into the system. This
could be a combination of product & channel/ or anything decided
mutually between Drona Pay and the external system
The created classes are displayed once we enter the Class
Management section. Here we can search through all the records
pertaining to different columns. The Table includes information
including:
● CLASS: Name of the class created
● REMARKS: comments on the class creation
● STATUS: Approved/Rejected
● LAST UPDATE: Most recent change made to the class
27 |',17,'2b4826cb-8e50-42ef-81c0-de558d4e6197');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',28,'5.2.1 Add/ edit/Delete class
● Click on the “add class” button to start creating a new
class or “edit”/ “View”/”Delete” icons
● For adding a new class ,enter the class under the
Transaction Class field. It is an input text field
● Select the Channel ID and Product ID. The Product ID
signifies the mode/instrument through which the payment
is made, e.g. UPI,IMPS, NEFT RTGS. Whereas Channel ID is
the medium through which the transaction is facilitated
e.g. API, ONLINE, POS, ATM.
● Next we need to select the decision to which the class
is supposed to be mapped with, that can be done by
choosing the decision from the Default Decision drop
down menu.
● The Payer/payee side registration can be set as
Mandatory/Non Mandatory.Selecting a side to be mandatory
requires the payer/payee side to be onboarded and
present in the Drona Pay masters before evaluating the
incoming transaction
● Once the Changes are made the user can click on send for
approval button for the changes to be verified by the
checker.
5.3 Decision Level Management
The Decision is based on the risk associated where the configured
decisions are built on a set of rules.
28 |',17,'a1568416-60da-45d6-a523-f59f6a593642');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',29,'Similar to the Class Management section the created decisions are
also displayed in the Decision Level Management, and can be
filtered through accordingly.
5.3.1 Edit/add Decision
● Click on the “edit” icon in front of the decision that
needs to be changed. To add a new Decision click on the
“ADD DECISION” button.
● In the Edit/Add Decision screen provide a Decision name
and details related to it in the relevant fields.
● Select Product ID from the Decision from the Product ID
dropdown menu, including options like CARD,IMPS,
NEFT,RTGS etc.
● Select how the scoring Aggregation must be
performed(Max,Min,Sum).
● Type: Real Time/Batch.
● Set the Final score setting according to the desired
requirements and configure remarks, status & workflow
details
29 |',17,'b39e296c-6300-42c8-b745-b2638ed85be1');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',30,'5.4 Rule Management
Upon entering the Rule Management section a summary table of
decisions is previewed to the user. From under the action column
of the table the user can either Edit or View the rules the
decision is made up of by clicking on the edit or view buttons
respectively.
5.4.1 Editing rules
Upon clicking the edit button, we are directed to the first
screen of editing rules. There are two sections under this
screen namely Select Rules and Manage Rules For:<Name of the
selected decision>
30 |',17,'374542cf-e068-4847-89c3-aa73fd9e2e9a');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',31,'Select Rules:
The main function of the select rule section is to add rules
to the selected decision. The rules can be searched for by
entering their names using the search bar present on the top.
The rules can also be searched for by making use of the
filter right next to the search bar. Rule filtering can be
performed by adding values like:
● Customer Type: Selecting the type of the customer like
Issuer, Processor, Bank, UPI and BNPL
● Side: Payer or Payee
● Rule Category: Selecting the category of the rule
from Value, Count, Velocity, MCC etc
The Rules are also segregated under several tabs, clicking on
the rule type tab will display all the rules under it.
Various Rule types include:
● Transaction based
● Behaviour based
● IP based
● User based
● Custom
The rules can be added to the Decision by clicking on the
plus and right arrow button given in front of each rule.
31 |',17,'1929a73b-32ce-4b29-abeb-96062c6543d5');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',32,'5.4.2 Manage Rules (Editing)
Edit rule section consists of all the rules that are
configured for the selected Decision with rule viewing and
editing options available for each of them. The thresholds
set for each rule are displayed along with Failscore.
To edit the rules, click on the edit button post which the
user is redirected to the Edit Rule screen.
Edit Rule screen is divided into two parts:
Rule Info: Consists of Rule Name, Rule Description, version
of the rule and information whether the rule is active or
not.
Rule Details: This is the section where the rule can be
configured. It consists of 3 sections under it, which are:
● Rule Builder: Drona Pay has integrated Blockly for
creating a drag and drop code block environment for
creation and editing of rules. The rules can be created
using:
○ various input options like variable, string,
array, dictionary etc,
○ Logical operators like <(less than),>(greater
than),!= (not equal to)etc
○ Boolean Numeric and string blocks
○ It also includes coded blocks for Profile(Vpa,
account, transaction etc), Realtime, Rule and
transaction.
32 |',17,'bcb2fb7d-c06a-4f6a-99d6-dacaaa239ff9');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',33,'● JSON View: All the changes made in Blockly rule builder
are implemented in a JSON format and can be viewed under
this section.
● Thresholds: In the threshold section the user can make
alterations to the default threshold values.
○ Default Rule Threshold:
■ Type: Weather the rule should trigger an
alert or block a transaction
■ Success score/ Fail Score: these are scored
with respect to the rule and are presented
when the rule is triggered.
■ Remarks: Remarks for success and failure can
be added.
● User Defined Thresholds: The threshold value for
transaction count and value can be changed
33 |',17,'26da8924-287c-4b08-b153-ac216d5fa50e');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',34,'5.5 List
The list tab helps create and manage black, grey and white lists.
The main screen table displays all the necessary information with
regards to various fields and whether they are black/ whitelisted,
Steps to add a list:
● Click on the “ADD LIST” button on the screen, post which the
Add List screen will appear.
● Select the type of list (Black or Grey) from the Type drop
down list.
● From the Field drop down list select the field which will be
affected by the Black or Grey list eg Payee Account, Payer
Account etc.
34 |',17,'f953b8ee-3a5b-42de-8e81-2efae39f405f');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',35,'● Enter the effective date range for the list in the Start Date
and End Date field.
● Next enter the value which needs to be blocked ,the source of
the lists and, since the list is being added, the user will
have to add a Maker remark since the addition would later be
approved by the checker.
● After saving, the list can be previewed under the List tab.
Steps to add White List:
● Click on the “ADD WHITELIST” button.
● Enter the effective date range for the list in the Start Date
and End Date field.
● Under the Value field add the value corresponding to the
Field which needs to be whitelisted.
● Additional conditions can be configured for adding fields to
the whitelist by clicking on the “+Rule” button and can be
grouped with other conditions using the “+Group” button in
the “Rule Creation” section.
● Right next to the rule configuration is how the rule code
would be implemented.
● After adding the “Maker Remark” the list created can be sent
for approval.
35 |',17,'bcb00bee-5ca3-4ed2-beac-45a66bf9fabe');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',36,'5.6 RT Window
Windows allow to capture a specific set or a group transaction
under a specific time window, the specifications can be set for
the payer or payee side.
The RT window table consists of the following information:
● WIN ID: Unique window ID
● NAME: Name of the Window.
● DURATION: P1D/P2D
● REMARKS: Any remarks associated with the created window.
● STATUS: Approved/Rejected
● LAST UPDATE: Last update date and time of the window.
● ACTION: View or delete the window.
36 |',17,'a23dd27f-9607-4cf4-9a58-b0bbb70375ca');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',37,'5.6.1 Adding a Window
Steps to add a Window:
● Click on the “ADD WINDOW” button.
● Once redirected to the Add Window screen Provide with
the unique Window Id, Window Name, Window Duration and a
count for the Window.
● Entering expressions:
○ Select expression: Defines the field that needs to
be aggregated.
○ Where expression: Defines the filter criteria.
○ Group by expression: For payer and payee ID
aggregation, it can be performed on VPA ID and
account ID.
● The changes can be sent for approval (Maker-checker).
5.7 RT Observation
The RT Observation table consists of the following information:
● OBS ID: Unique observation ID.
● NAME: Name of the observation.
● DURATION: P1D,PT15M,PT5M etc.
● REMARKS: Remarks associated with created observation.
● STATUS: Approved/Rejected.
● LAST UPDATE: Last update date and time of the
observation.
● ACTION: View or delete.
37 |',17,'604f8180-36de-49f0-80ea-613c089145b3');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',38,'5.7.1 Adding an Observation
Steps to add an Observation:
● Click on the “ADD OBSERVATION” button.
● Provide details regarding Observation Name, Observation
Duration in ISO Temporal duration format
● Select the aggregation type from the Aggregation Type
dropdown list consisting of COUNT, COUNT IF, SUM, SUM IF
● From the Window Id drop down list select the window for
which the observation needs to be created.
● Entering expressions:
○ Select expression: Defines the field that needs to
be aggregated.
○ Where expression: Defines the filter criteria.
○ Group by expression: For payer and payee ID
aggregation, it can be performed on VPA ID and
account ID.
● The changes can be sent for approval (Maker-checker).
38 |',17,'98a80b42-0502-4449-a3d6-caf558e8b26e');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',39,'5.8 Historic Profile
The Historic Profile consists of all the parameters created, the
Master data associated with them, the data type of the parameter.
They can be viewed under the Historic profile.
5.8.1 Adding an Aggregation
Steps to add a Custom Aggregation:
1. Click on the “ADD CUSTOM AGGREGATION” button.
2. Provide details regarding Profile Name, Level at which this
profile needs to be computed (Account, VPA, MCC), Mode i.e.
frequency at which it should be computed, Data Type,
39 |',17,'51125457-5a1b-45ee-8183-e0a85fdb7ad1');
INSERT INTO agents.user_manual(doc_name,version,date,pageid,page_content,itenantid,docid) VALUES ('User Manual',1,'2025-03-24',40,'Aggregation Type (TotalValue, AvgValue, TotalCount,
AvgCount,Custom), Window in ISO Temporal duration format
3. One can then go to the Editor tab to configure the query for
the aggregate. Example queries have been listed to support
